<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1410,1772]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Described from an unspecified number of females from 
<collectingCountry box="[820,885,1410,1436]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Zaire</collectingCountry>
, a few specimens have also been studied from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,242,1448,1474]" name="Angola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Angola</collectingCountry>
. This species is unusual in having so many setae on the margin of the forewing clavus and posterior margin of the pronotum.
</paragraph>
